The '''Association of Independent Colleges and Universities in Massachusetts (AICUM), ''' is a grouping of [[Higher education accreditation|accredited]], independent, [[private university|private college]]s and [[Private university|universities]] in the state of [[Massachusetts]]. The Association advocates in public policy forums on behalf of its member institutions.<ref name=About>{{cite web|title=About AICUM|url=http://www.aicum.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=17&Itemid=48|work=aicum.org|publisher=AICUM|accessdate=13 November 2013}}</ref>

AICUM is headquartered in [[Boston, Massachusetts]], and it was established by a panel of university presidents. Its current president is Richard Doherty.<ref name=Contact>{{cite web|title=Contact Us|url=http://www.aicum.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=137&Itemid=205|work=aicum.org|publisher=AICUM|accessdate=13 November 2013}}</ref> AICUM is a member of the Coalition for College Cost Savings, and the [[National Association of Independent Colleges and Universities]]<ref name=CCCS>{{cite web|last=Werner |first=Jessie |title=AICUM Joins CCCS |url=http://www.thecoalition.us/news/2013/05/20/aicum-joins-cccs.632123 |work=thecoalition.us |publisher=CCCS |accessdate=13 November 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113212616/http://www.thecoalition.us/news/2013/05/20/aicum-joins-cccs.632123 |archivedate=13 November 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref name=NAICU>{{cite web|title=National Association of Independent College and University State Executives (NAICUSE) |url=http://www.naicu.edu/member_center/naicuse.asp |work=naicu.edu |publisher=NAICU |accessdate=13 November 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131114072549/http://www.naicu.edu/member_center/naicuse.asp |archivedate=14 November 2013 |df= }}</ref>

