la '''Escuela Secundaria Tecnica Quimica Industrial y Minera''' - '''ESTQIM''' (Technical, Chemical, Industrial and Mining High School), [[argentina|Argentine]] high-school located in [[Malargüe]], [[Mendoza Province]]. The school currently has 800 students, and it is one of the most popular schools in the city, competing against the schools ISMA and Aborigen Americano.

The school offers a curriculum mainly based on chemistry, industrial, and other technical subjects. Students must choose an orientation after their 3rd year, for either [[chemistry]] (3 more years) or [[tourism]] (2 more years). Chemistry involves technical and engineering classes. while tourism is more like a normal [[Bachelor's degree|baccalaureate]] with some inclinations towards tourism and advertising.

