'''Faculty Research Awards''' 2018 were awarded to academic researchers across 24 disciplines by the Indian Union Minister of Human Resource Development [[Prakash Javadekar]] on 20 March in [[New Delhi]]. The awards were hosted by news magazine [[Careers360]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/5-pu-teachers-in-running-for-research-awards-on-mar-20/articleshow/63377650.cms|title=5 PU teachers in running for research awards on Mar20|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref> The awards recognize the efforts of those in the field of academic research in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.careers360.com/faculty-research-awards-254-researchers-shortlisted-across-24-disciplines|title=Faculty Research Awards: 254 researchers shortlisted across 24 disciplines|website=News.careers360.com|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref> The award carries a cash prize and a citation.

The awardees were chosen on the basis of their academic and research output in [[Scopus]] indexed journals, [[citation index]] and [[h-index]] for the period 2015-17.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.careers360.com/union-hrd-minister-prakash-javadekar-present-faculty-research-awards-march-20|title=Union HRD Minister Prakash Javadekar to present ‘Faculty Research Awards’ on March 20|website=News.careers360.com|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref>

