'''The Hindu College''' (formerly the Swami Purnananda Secondary School) is a Hindu secondary school in [[Cove and John]] in the [[Demerara-Mahaica]] region (Region 4) of [[Guyana]].<ref name=Knews2010>{{cite news|last=Knews|title=Kaieteur News|url=http://www.kaieteurnewsonline.com/2010/08/24/cove-john-hindu-college-enjoys-csec-success/|accessdate=6 September 2012|newspaper=Kaieteur News|date=24 August 2010}}</ref><ref name=GC2010 />
==History==
The Hindu College was founded in 1957 by [[Swami Purnananda]] - the [[Hindu]] leader who founded the [[Guyana Sevashran Sangha]] movement in the mid-twentieth century.<ref name=Persaud2010>{{cite news|last=Persaud|first=Nowrang|title=Hindu College employs teachers of all religions and races|url=http://www.kaieteurnewsonline.com/2010/12/15/hindu-college-employs-teachers-of-all-religions-and-races/|accessdate=6 September 2012|newspaper=Kaieteur News|date=15 December 2010}}</ref><ref name=Jones2007>{{cite book|last=Jones|first=Constance|title=Encyclopedia of Hinduism|year=2007|publisher=Infobase Publishing|isbn=9780816075645|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OgMmceadQ3gC&pg=PA175&lpg=PA175&dq=Swami+Purnananda+guyana&source=bl&ots=lTXvz0Feqc&sig=lN4_1t1GCDynQ7PdFZyxNIhrRz8&hl=en#v=onepage&q=Swa|author2=James D. Ryan|accessdate=6 September 2012|page=175|chapter=Guyana}}</ref> In 2010, the college recorded a 100% pass-rate for students taking the [[Caribbean Secondary Education Certificate]] (CSEC).<ref name=Knews2010 /><ref name=GC2010>{{cite news|last=Anon|title=Hindu College scores one hundred percent passes|url=http://www.guyanachronicleonline.com/site/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=17859%3Ahindu-college-scores-one-hundred-percent-passes&Itemid=12|accessdate=6 September 2012|newspaper=Guyana Chronicle|date=27 August 2010}}</ref> In 2010, the Hindu College received a $300,000 donation to fund the establishment of a learning resource centre that was named the Zara Learning Centre.<ref name=SN2010>{{cite news|last=Stabroek Staff|title=Cove and John Hindu College gets $300,000 resource centre|url=http://www.stabroeknews.com/2010/archives/02/08/cove-and-john-hindu-college-gets-us300000-resource-centre/|accessdate=6 September 2012|newspaper=Stabroek News|date=8 February 2010}}</ref>
