The '''École nationale des sciences appliquées de Tétouan''' (National school of applied sciences of Tetouan) is a public [[engineering]] school in [[Morocco]] established in September, 2008.<ref> {{fr}} http://ensate.uae.ma/Portail/?page_id=97</ref> The school is located in [[Tetouan]], Morocco. It is part of the National Schools of Applied Sciences-[[Écoles nationales des sciences appliquées|ENSA]] and [[Abdelmalek Essaâdi University]].
==Mission== The school's main goals are:<ref>{{fr}} http://www.uae.ma/ensate/Portail/?page_id=97</ref> * training and preparing qualified engineers in an array of engineering disciplines (see below) both theoretically and practically in order to satisfy the needs of economical and social developments both regionally and nationally. * Advancing scientific and technological researches. * Establishing a cooperation framework with industrial, socio-economical, and scientific decision makers regionally, nationally, and internationally.
==Programmes offered== *Computer Engineering *Telecommunication and Networks Engineering *Mechatronics Engineering *Supply Chain Engineering *Civil Engineering
